    <text id="R137714764T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Union General William Averell reports to General Darius Couch, commanding at
                    Chambersburg, concerning scouting reports by his men in July, 1864.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Maj.-Gen. COUCH,<lb/> Chambersburg, Pa.:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1864-07-27">July 27, 1864.</date>
                        <name type="place">HAGERSTOWN, MD.,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>
                <p>One of my aides at Clear Spring reports, at 11.30 a. m., nothing but rumors. One
                    of my squadrons was on the way to McCoy's Ferry, and others went toward Cherry
                    Run. At 12.30 Col. Moore, Eighth Ohio, reports that about thirty rebels crossed
                    at Back Creek this morning. About 400 were engaged in destroying Back Creek
                    bridge. I am sure of complete information soon, when I will forward it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>WM. W. AVERELL,<lb/> Brig.-Gen.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
